\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 This small shop at Beechcliffe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How long did you stay at the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Twenty years. Just about, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Which is the house that you remember the best?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well I remember them all. Yes. Of course Long Lee in schooldays - yes, yes. And that was only one up and one down, well you could say two up but one was a very small one, still it had to be - a bedroom for my brother, for the boy you see. And th
e other - had to - was a big bedroom and - two girls in one bed and there were only two then, the third one was - born up there, the fourth one was born at Beechcliffe, see, the youngest of these. Mm. That's what you wanted.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How many brothers and sisters did you have, could you tell us their birth order?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. Yes. Had me brother, was born the fourteenth of March and he's not quite two years older than me, so - it would be - 18 - about 1890, it would be - 18 - 88 wouldn't it. Yes, that's right, on
ly his is March, you see. I think - I think so, it wouldn't be the ninth, 89, March. Could have been 89, does that matter to it, a year, no.
\par 
