\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And he just managed this smallholding?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, that's right. Yes. Mother made butter and - we had a cow or two. No more than two.
 Oh and the - he had a little smithy and he made - nails and - he - I don't know whether they made horseshoes, but he certainly made nails. If you go back in Silsden's history - there was a lot of nail making in - Silsden, yes - it - do you want all this 
d
own, it - it has a nickname to the Old Silsden people, they called it the neck end of Sheffield. A by name, because - it was the Sheffield kind of work - that was being carried out in Silsden. Nails for horseshoes. Nails for anything. And they had a small
 smithy and made nails as well as the little smallholding.
