\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes. Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 With the trucks packed with absolutely nothing but wringers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Are they? Oh - yes, and in fact they'd be wood. They'd go from Connor Lane - down to the railway. Yes, yes, that's right. Mm. And they had horses and wagons as well to take them. Yes. Yes, it was all horse - traffic - then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think actually during the war they went over to munitions, is that right?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So he would be on munitions during the 14/18 war?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. 14/18 war. We were on Beechcliffe. And - ye
s, he - he would still - he would still be in the section - which had the wood in it - but he did because - I remember occasionally - meeting odd people who said, I worked for your father during the war. Now I don't remember what they were doing - there, 
b
ut there were some girls who worked - under me father, in this warehouse place, which had been just a store place. They still might have been doing something connected with wood but - they'd some machinery in there and they - they made something for the w
ar effort. Yes, they did.
