dings - in service, as a maidservant. At Cravens. Which was - what - what is now a - a hotel or a guest house. But as far as I know it was that house. It was the Craven family who had a mill in Long Mill Lane, and - one - two of mother's older sisters - c
a
me first, and then - because they were there - they could bring this - younger sister. So far as I know she was only - twelve and a half - or so - when she left home, which was - not far from Sinderford where I met me husband, that's the remote connection
 you see that comes back. She - they moved from Mommouth to this - area, which are on the edge of the Forest of Dene, and she came up to be in service, at Craven's.
