\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, she didn't - no. After she was married she didn't do any more - going out to work. She wasn't really very strong. And
 then she had us fairly quickly, you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So she didn't do any more jobs then until you took this shop at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. She did the occasional day's washing for somebody, but I don't think - yes, occasionally.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was nothing regular?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh no, nothing regular, just - now and again to - just a little bit of extra pocket money or would - buy a bit of extra clothing or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So here next job was looking after the shop at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you also helped?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were also a shop assistant in this shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In - in this shop at thirteen, helped generally, house duties and shop, you know, anything, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So your mother was never really strong enough to tackle a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She'd - no, she couldn't. No. She - she'd had us, she did the housework you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So she never did another job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She never went out to work for money. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you took a bigger shop didn't you after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, in Keighley, in the town. Th
at was for the benefit of my brother. Because he was out of work. A period after - he - he was apprenticed to be a butcher. But in those days they only wanted them - as apprentices but they didn't want them as fully fledged men. And - no, and - he didn't 
-
 find a job anywhere, he tried a small shop of his own, but he couldn't make it go. It was too small. And - so he turned over to the drapery - from our little shop at Beechcliffe he took drapery out and - hawked it round the countryside. Yes. There - ther
e
's no other - way in those days, and - then it - this little shop - was vacant in Keighley, and - he said, would I go in it - to help him, if he took it on. And then he could think about getting married. Because he couldn't - get married on what he was ma
king - going around, he made a round - up, a good round, but not enough to get married and support a - a home on you see. So that's how we did.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What year would this be?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It would be - 1912. Yes. I was twenty-two. That's right. It was a small shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was the same line of business as you'd had at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh yes, it was definitely drapery. Yes. We started in quite a very small way but - we did sewing you know behind the scenes. Any plain sewing, anything that anybody - wanted we tack
led anything and everything. You know, if anybody wanted something making we were - only too pleased to make it to - supply the material you see. And everything, and we just slowly built it up. And then the war came. And me brother had to go in the war. S
o
 we managed alone, that's when me next younger sister - came in it to help me, this is - Mrs - Nicholson. Not the one in between. And - well she - I think she was still at the Beechcliffe shop helping mother, because she was a war widow in the first war. 
S
he was a war widow - I was going to say fairly early. She wasn't really but - me - me brother didn't go into the war 'til 1917, well by that time she was a war widow - her - her husband had gone in bang at the beginning, before they were married, he was -
 that kind of a person, he volunteered and went in you see in the first - early years of the war.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She'd be very young widow wouldn't she?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, I think she was twenty-three. She might have been twenty-four, she was twenty-three when she was marrie
d to him, and he was a serving soldier then, you know, had a leave to get married. And - I don't know whether it was just the year after, they courted from being seventeen. They'd have a long courtship but they - didn't have a long time after - married li
fe before he was killed. But - I don't remember exactly - which year - it might have been two years - after, when - when he was killed out in France.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I should like to ask you now about life at home when you were a child, the time up to when you left school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think the best house to talk about is the one at Long Lee.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, definitely. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already told me that there were just four rooms, two up, two down.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Well that counted - a little kitchen downstairs and a little bedroom above it. And the main living room and the main bedroom.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you had just a living room and a very small kitchen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 A large bedroom and a very small bedroom?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was there an attic?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 A cellar?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Oh well - there was a little pantry down about four steps. It wasn't a proper cellar. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did anyone else besides your parents and your brother and sisters live in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No relatives or lodgers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother pay anyone to help in the house?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was the washing done at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm. And the baking. Yes. Mm, mm. Mm, yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother or father mend or make the family's clothes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The what?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother mend or make the family's clothes?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Mother did. Yes. She did all the sewing. She made a lot of our clothes. Almost all of them I should think. Father mended shoes or clogs as the case - might be.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He never made them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, he repaired them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The clothes that she made for you, would it be new material that she used for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They wouldn't be cut down, second}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737737\charrsid15471180  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 hand things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well - a little of both, but she did buy new materials - to make - what we called our better clothes, I did have
 - I did have some - cut down ones that had been other people's, I remember, but - me sister flatly refused to wear mine cut down. There was a row once. Not - not for me to have a new one and her to have a cut down one, no. But she managed.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember ever actually being bought clothes, being taken to a shop and bought dresses and things when you were still at school?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think they were always made. I remember buying hats. And she'd even trim those, she'd buy - see trimmings, plain hats. It's
 - I'll tell you what she did buy for us was - coats. We once had new coats. It was always the two of us, the nearer in age, that I remember - you see, because it - it was mine - it - whatever one had the other had the two.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You and your sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. Yes. The - the younger ones were quite separate, mother made or bought for them - when - when they needed - it had nothing to do with me so I don't remember it so plainly.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you and your next sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Next sister.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you got the new coats where did she buy them from?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 At the Co-op. At the Co-op then yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you got new shoes where would you get those from?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Mostly in the bottom of the market. There was a special shop there that made - good sound - sensible shoes
. And we often went there for shoes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about clogs, did they make clogs as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No, we didn't get clogs there, that was shoes, definitely. Clogs was mostly the Co-op again, there's a Co-op on Parkwood Street where we went to school, and the 
clogs - I think would be bought there, we certainly went there for - repairs, irons and things. Yes, I think they'd be bought there as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When were you either bought or made new clothes, was it just when you needed them or was there a certain time 
of each year when you had a new outfit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well - we - we had new clothes - for - Easter to Whitsuntide - if it could be arranged, if not I'm afraid we waited until it could, you see. We had that to be made do two years many a time, but it wasn't a yearly event that you got new clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was when it was essential?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was when it was essential, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did the same apply to shoes as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, clogs for school, and shoes for - best. But to do as long as we could 'til we - grew out of them in many cases you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your father help your mother with any of the jobs in the house? Such as cleaning and cooking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well - he did if she was ill. If she wasn't feeling well, he wasn't a great one for cleaning much but - he would c
ertainly - begin to cook - if she was ill, he'd make us our breakfast or - Sunday dinner if he was at home - and he'd do anything in that way, he wasn't a - a great man form - washing clothes and that sort of thing. He'd do the cooking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would he do the washing up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, presumably, I don't just remember, but if she was too - too poorly to make it he'd have to do the washing up as well.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about fires in the morning, did he always lay the fire, whether she was ill or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well often, w
e'll put it like that. Often. Mind we were tutored to do it as we got a bit older you see. We - yes, because - it was coal fires and - you know - the ashes - if the ashes were very warm it didn't take you many minutes to - to get some sticks going and get
ting another fire out of it. So we were tutored to do that - more or less before - before I was thirteen. Yes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about decorating the house and repairs to the house and improvements, did he ever do anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Me mother drove him.
 It brings back memories, he was forced. Mother would decorate, papering. Yes. Yes, mother would do that, she was quite good at it. But - father - couldn't do it to her satisfaction so she said, get out of the way and let me do it. But I think he would do
 - any - large - large repairs. He'd do anything with wood at any rate. Because he considered that he did a day's work from six o'clock in the morning 'til nearly six at night - that was all that mattered you see, and Saturdays. Saturday mornings.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When
 you and your brother and sister were quite small do you remember him helping with doing things for you, such as dressing you or undressing you or bathing you, things like that? To give your mother a rest or if she was feeling ill.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think he would d
o it if - he sat there in the chair and watched. He was there, he didn't go out. Oh he was always there - he'd be - he'd - it'd be more of a case of - if it was necessary - he would step in and do it but - not normally, no, not normally. Normally it was h
is rest in the evening.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did he ever read to you or tell you stories?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh yes. Oh he'd do that. He was - he was - more of a reader than my mother was - it - we didn't have a lot of books but - he would - he would not only read to us he would tell us -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Stories from memory?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, from memory, and where he'd been and - all sorts o}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737737\charrsid15471180 
f experiences in the past. Humo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 rous and otherwise, he - he would tell us lots of things that - he'd done as a boy and a youth and - lot - lots of things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you were very small did he ever take you out without your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did he ever let her go out and look after you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. If mother went out shopping into Keighley, or Long Lee to go into Keighley, father looked after the
 youngest ones. You see you'd to - when we were old enough we'd to go along to help to carry - for her, but if she was out shipping - in - into Keighley, father looked after the - the house and the young ones. Yes.
