ee, if - before we learnt to do that we'd get up with father when he was going to work, the oldest of us, mother'd still stay in bed a bit longer. Well there was the period when the - younger one was born, not the youngest but the other younger one you se
e
, and I suppose she wasn't too good at that time and - that'd be the time when - I'd - be wakened - I was eight, yes. Yes, well - then more often father would light the fire. And then that be - I - I might be - I might be saying a bit too much but - yes, 
I
 - I don't - yes, I remember one time she had a sister ill, and went away and left me for the whole day. When Mary was two, and I'd be ten. But it was - very necessary, this sister was very ill, and it was at Silsden. And I was left in charge for myself a
nd that little girl - from her going after breakfast - 'til father came home at night. And -
