\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, the - youngest wasn't born. Oh she was at school. She was at school and get her di
nner at school. That - so that was the only way mother could manage, she said, I must stay out - at home and look after Mary who was about two, a little toddler, and I must be very careful and mind the fire and - because R - I did something - that brings 
i
t very vividly to me memory, she wore little clogs, and - there was a little bit of a - mess, and - I was - I was cleaning up the clogs and I threw the clogs on the fire instead. I fished them off right quick. So I mean - I was definitely left in charge t
hat day, but it was very essential there, she wouldn't - neither parent would have left us if it wasn't something - very essential.
\par 
