\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In the period before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes. Oh up to and before 1919 well you see I was twenty-nine then - in that year. Oh well there was our grandparents funerals, y
ou see. The grandparents at Silsden only me father went and mother. We were left in charge of one another. We were old enough to be left in charge then. Yes, because she didn't have Mary, it was in between. And - oh they might have some other relative - o
r
 a neighbour stopped with us, that I don't remember. I remember that they went - to these two funerals at Silsden, because - one was - my grand - mother, can't remember grandfather at Silsden, he died before I was born I think, but the other was one of my
 mother's sisters, an auntie, and there was only a month or two between them, you see. And - and so I remember those two funerals. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you didn't go to either of them did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I went to - I went to me mother's - father and mother, my grandparents in Keighley. I went to those funerals, I was -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They came to live up in Keighley did they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh - oh yes, they come up - yes, before - they came up after the sisters came in service. Came - the - the family came, the lot came, yes. Yes,
 oh they were all in Keighley, then. Of course I'd only been speaking about me mother you see, coming up with these other sisters. Yes, they followed, because mother said - if she'd already got there here and - and the son, who was - who was on the railwa
y, she might as well pack up the home and - and come with the rest. There were more opportunities for them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So can you remember the funeral of either your grandfather or grandmother on your mother's side?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, definitely. Because I went to the on
e - well I went to them both, but - me grandfather - died - when I was fifteen, and that was the time that mother was expecting the youngest, you see, who was born - when I was nearly sixteen. And - so I had to go to that in place of me mother, you see. A
nd -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Can you tell me any of the details of the funeral, what happened, who came, how many guests, were they in mourning?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh they were in mourning, it was nec - well almost considered necessary. They lived in a house with a sitting room, a living 
room and a sitting room down Lawcombe, and the coffin was in the - sitting room, in the sitting room you see there, and - the family - because there was - a fairly big family - and - there were some in the one room and some in the other, it was a case of 
- come in and stand up. You know, there were - there were only - what seating accommodation - was taken by my aunties and - uncles who were older. And grandma.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How many people were there, how many guests?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Thirty or forty. I should think. I mean t
here was two from my family, me and me brother and there was - three from another family that I remember, and there'd be three from the family who lived in along with grandfather and grandmother. And - and there's - there'd be a few neighbours, yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And they all had black on did they, most of the people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, most of the people. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You all assembled at the house, then did you walk to the church or did you have carriages to take you to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There's some carriages because it came to the cemetery, we didn't walk all the way to the cemetery. Keighley cemetery.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you go to the church before you went to the cemetery?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Didn't go to a church, the - the minister came to the house and had a service in the house. And - I c
an't distinctly remember the carriages, but there must have been because - we came on to - Keighley came - the - they was in Keighley cemetery you see. And of course grandmother's - I was - twenty-two I think when me grandmother died. So there was another
 - similar funeral. There were fewer uncles and aunts and more grandchildren. You see, there'd been - more coming up.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did even the grandchildren wear black?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. It - perhaps not dead black, but - definitely - oh black. But I mean you might wear 
black with a white blouse perhaps or - or a very dark grey. They bought black - for grandfather and grandmother. Yes. Yes, black new clothes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about after the actual burial, did you all just go home or did you have a meal at someone's house or a tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
We didn't - we went - we went home - or a few - those who lived out of Keighley would go - to the house and the - old - the other aunties or somebody would make a - there would be somebody would come to our house, 'cos at that time we we
re living on Beechcliffe you see, so some would come there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 For a tea?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you taken out visiting neighbours or friends or relations when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Who would take you, would it be mother or father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Mostly mother. Mostly mother. Father wasn't a great visitor. He - he wanted to stop at home. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you taken shopping, you've already told me that you had to take it in turns?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right. Yes we were taken shopping. My brother and m
yself, as being the oldest, and later on he became a butcher, apprenticed to a butcher, well it would be my - me and the other sister in turns. Always one.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you used to have to help to carry all the shopping for the week, right from Keighley up to Long Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There weren't any trams or anything like that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no. Oh no, you carried it, yes. That - that's why it needed two you see, it was too much for one. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever go out with just your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes - summer wal
ks. You know, over the moors. That would be going out with father. I - I should say about the shopping though, it didn't involve all the shopping. The grocery was brought up. The Co-op had a delivery. The shopping we were buying was meat and - orange - fr
u
it, yes, anything you bought in the market. Yes. Yes. That's right. Yes, they delivered every week an order and it'd be father's hen food and - as well, you see, everything. I - I thought you could - I could just see us - absolutely burdened down if we go
t to - bring everything, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember any other outings with your parents, perhaps on Bank holidays?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We - we had one outing - it might have been one a year, I can remember two. When the works - gave an outing to Blackpool. And - I thi
nk - there were free tickets for man and wife and they had to pay a small amount for children. I'm not sure. But we went - on this trip, day trip to Blackpool. And }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737737\charrsid15471180 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180  Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737737\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
scales, yes, a railway trip. I won't say whether they booked so many coaches or the whole train, that I don't know. I've no idea, but we went, I can remember being there. At the sea.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What would you do at the seaside, would you play games?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Play on the sands when the tide was out. And - go in the - tower, we definitely went in t
he aquarium and the tower, oh that's one place father would - glory in - taking us and - and - enjoy himself in going you see. And - and we had a sail, on a boat. Yes, we went out on the water on a boat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would this be at Parish Feast Week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was a - it was an extra one, it was an extra Saturday. When they didn't work. Yes. They - they had it specially, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And it was paid for by Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid7737737\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 scales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Except for the children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well it - the most of it was paid for, I - just h
ow - how much - mother and father and to pay for us I don't distinctly remember. It - it might even have been allowed tickets for the children and just buy your own food. I'm not sure of the details but most of it was paid for by the firm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever go away for a holiday to stay?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Never?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How old were you when you first went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Seventeen. With a friend. Yes. My father wouldn't go and mother said she couldn't go with three or four children, and so we didn't go, and we could wait until we were old enough to go by ourselves and so -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So when you were seventeen you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I went to Morecambe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Where did you go to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 To Morecambe. With a friend, for about four or five days, not for a whole week I think. This one girlfriend. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did this become a regular thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. It became a regular thing because three of us became friends instead of two, after that year, and the three of us went around everywhere together. We went lots of holidays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you always go to Morecambe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh no. No, no, we - we decided we - we didn't want to always go to Morecambe, we went to Blackpool, went to Blackpool two years running, and then - after that we - we used to have a little - meeting between ourselves you know
, and then we went to Cleethorpes and we went to - Bridlington. I don't think we went to Scarborough. Went to Bridlington, Cleethorpes, and then we got in touch with the - holiday homes - Christian Endeavour Holiday Homes, and we went there. I was twenty-
f
our - first time I went there. And we went there two years and then they got married, got courting and got married, so I found - other friends you see. And - oh I went to Scotland to Christian Endeavour Holiday Home, I didn't go to Wales. And - I went hol
idays each year somewhere, but - we varied the places pretty much. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I'll just talk about this first holiday you went to Morecambe when you were 17.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, to Morecambe. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There was just you and this friend?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What activities would there be when you were on holiday, what sort of thing would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well we went in the water, swimming. We'd gone to the swimming baths at - at home you see, from last - last year or two at school and afterwards. And - wed' learnt
 to swim. I wasn't a strong swimmer but we learnt to swim, so that was one of the things - the two of us did. We kept very much just together. And - of course we'd to buy our own food and take it in to be cooked. At this house you know, and so we'd to - r
u
n back to get dressed and - and - I - I think we should just - go sitting on the pier in the afternoon or - have a little coach trip, there were a few little coach trips - beginning in those days, not - not very - I - I remember the first one from - Bridl
ington. I don't really remember one from Morecambe. So -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And in the evenings what would you do?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Just go walks I think. We'd - wait a minute, my - I mean when it was Blackpool we'd go to the tower. When it was Morecambe - if there were any concert
s we should have gone to concerts. She was musical. Was fond of music. I can't distinctly remember - we'd spend most of the time just walking, to and for on the front.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Could you tell me how you spent Saturdays in those days? I know you told me in the 
evenings you would help your mother bring the shopping home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about in the morning and afternoon would there be anything - any set pattern?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's going back to before I was thirteen? Yes. Well, occasionally we went down in the tow
n on our own with our own pocket money, occasionally, and - and - went - and of course we had a grandmother you know down - Lowcombe, you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You went there did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Down Emily Street in Lowcome, so therefore - we'd tuppence pock
et money because you walked, you could go to grandmother's and have some tea and you could - buy yourself - yes, oh yes, if you went you just said hello and walked in and - everybody was accepted. They'd say, how's your mother. Come along in and is your m
o
ther coming down after tea, have you to stop here 'til she comes or - or what are you doing. Yes. Yes - no, you'd - if you left home with freedom to come down by afternoon and go back again, somebody else coming down in the evening, all right, so long as 
you walked. It didn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about Sundays, what would you do on a Sunday when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well the Sunday school. Morning and afternoon, Sunday school, and - but not evening at Long Lee. Mother didn't - fancy it somehow, she 
didn't - she felt she wasn't made welcome, that's what they did in those days if they - if they weren't made welcome they first day they didn't bother to go any more. And of course father wasn't - he wasn't a church or chapel goer, and - so it was a case 
o
f walk - Sunday evening walks - so long as the weather was fine, always over - up over the moor, well then you came to Druids Altar or whether you went the other way and came - you could come back down into Long Lee - without going right to - Ingrow, you 
c
ould walk on the top and come down the hillside - several places, there, so it would be - a walk around with - reasonable time to come back again for suppertime. And in winter it was round the fire, it was either with the harmonium or just with books and 
- and games and that kind of thing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I've just asked you about different clothes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And you told me that you did have something best for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Best - best were always kept - for Sunday.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Shoes and everything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, really everything, yes. And second bests were worn which had been bests the year before, by that time we}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 d}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180  b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
e perhaps getting them each year - well perhaps I'm thinking ahead to when I was fourteen or fifteen, but anyhow best were best.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And that was just for Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Just for Sundays and - and perhaps the occasional - going out to visit you know with mother.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you allowed to play games, did you play games on a Sunday? You say you went to church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right. Yes. We were allowed
 to play indoor games, but we weren't allowed to go out and play on the roads, and - you know - or anything that might make a - a row, cause a lot of shouting - I don't really think we were allowed to go and play a ball outside on a Sunday. No. But - they
 weren't very strict weren't our parents about it. It might have been a case of you'll annoy the others.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you wouldn't say that your parents thought it wrong to work or play on a Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, they didn't think it wrong, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your parents attend a place of worship? You've already said that your father didn't. He didn't go to church or chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. No. Well at Long Lee we were too far away, me mother belonged to the Baptist, in the town, she was a Baptist you see, and it was too far a
way, because well, children were to consider, you know, when we came to live down in town that was where we went, afterwards, yes, but - we went to the little Wesleyans up - up there in our Sunday school days, but - mother stayed at home and father stayed
 at home, they - they didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They didn't go to either church or Sunday school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, not at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You said because your mother didn't feel welcome?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, that's right. During those years she didn't go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You went to the church in the morning and Sunday school in an afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well - it was really both Sunday school really I think - mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They were both at the Wesleyan?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Yes, mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were there ever any Sunday school outings at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Ye
s. We came to Newsholme Dene once. They were walking outings, that's one - and of course we had - the anniversary and we had the - the walking day which I think would be Whitsuntide when there was a field - a field day and field sports, and just walk arou
nd the district and sing at a - a few - special houses, and crossroads and that - by crossroads, I mean - where the school is now and - and there or - places like that.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Up at Long Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Up at Long Lee. That was what we called the walking day you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you have a brass band to play for you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. It couldn't afford it I don't think.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you went to Newsholme Dene, was that just an isolated incident?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That I remember. Yes, I don't remember -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You don't remember going every year?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, no I don't remember going every year.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you walk to Newsholme Dene?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. Yes, from Long Lee. We went - we went down Bodkin Hill and up - up Victoria Road and it was almost a straight road when you think of it. That was the way we were taken. Yes. Newsholme Dene.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What other social activities were organised by the chapel did you take part in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well there were things but I just can't remember - why - there - there was this - a tea, once - oh there was a prize giving, t
ea and prize giving. That would be one. And the concert you know, we'd, we would be in the concert. I used to recite. I wasn't a singer but I used to recite - in those days. And - and there'd be a tea - there'd be the harvest and there'd be a tea - a tea 
for that. And a - concert - in the evening. I don't remember - and the anniversary which was outside in the field. And of course I've said the Whitsuntide, and that was the same field. That was loaned to them. Those were the outstanding ones.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever have any socials in any evening, sort of dances?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so. Chapels didn't go in for dancing. Not in those days, they frowned on dancing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You belonged to the choir didn't you?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not me. Me sister. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did the chapel run any temperance club?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes, we did do that, we had - Band of Hope. That's right. That was where I did a bit of me reciting. Band of Hope, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What activities did the Band of Hope have?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 A meeting, a sing-song and a meeting at somebo
dy's - speak - to us. I don't remember anything more def - a weekday evening, yes, and those - this - few - songs which p}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
inted the Band of Hope message, songs and recitations you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you belong to any other club organised by the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Not - not up to that age. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not up 'til leaving school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right, well leaving school is when I also left Long Lee you see, and it all changed then, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was grace said at meals in your family?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you taught to say prayers at night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. When we were small. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever have family prayers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't marry until 1930?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Mm. I didn't meet my - my - I met the wrong ones. Yes. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say that your father took an interest in politics at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
A - a negative interest but he was definitely - a Conservative, a die hard, do not change. A boss's man, if you know what I mean by that. That's what they call him nowadays.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He admired the boss?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No - he believed - that the upper classes - were educated and therefore - they - should rule because they could rule, that the working men had not enough education. He didn't believe in the Labour party.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Each had it's own place?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That was - 
that was what we were - well that was what - father talked like that, as - and up to that age I - I couldn't care less, it didn't matter at all you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So these views he held, were they his own views or would you say that he got them partly from his own father, or parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
He got them partly from his own home surroundings. His - I never knew my grandfather on - on - my father's side - I gathered from my mother - that he also was so quiet a man grandmother was - the ruling party, and so it would 
be what grandmother said which - which went in their home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about your mother, did she have any political views at all or did she agree with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I don't think she quite agreed with him. But - they weren't obvious. You see there wasn
't a vote for women. There were - there were no arguments, she - she just said oh wait 'til you grow up and - do what you - please yourself when you grow up, think about it then. There's no need to bother now, it didn't - it wasn't as acute as it's become
 of later years. Not really.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So although you don't remember them arguing about you do have this opinion that she didn't agree entirely with your father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, she was - that little bit different - character, but she - she'd perhaps believed that -
 the working class could do with a few more benefits, you - you understand.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She felt things weren't as good as your father felt they were?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She wasn't well satisfied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She - she wasn't - well, she'd been in service you see
 in her young days, and the position had been the same there. The ups were up and the downs were downs. Considerably, although - she never grumbled at her conditions there, at all, she was well treated, she never grumbled at her conditions there but - I t
h
ink - me mother - if she'd been - twenty years later, she would have been a Liberal. I don't think she'd have been a - a proper Labour then. She would have been a Liberal, she wouldn't have been a Tory - who thought - the powers that be should remain the 
powers that be. Yes. Oh yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Can you remember your father or mother voting in a general election before 1919?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, they would. I mean I'd be twenty-nine then, definitely - voted in the general election. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Your mother as well?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, I think so, they might have had to - take her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Women got the vote in 1918.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Well she would go to vote. Yes, whether she voted with father or against. I wouldn't like to say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you think your father would have voted Conservative?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, I do.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You think that your mother may well have voted Liberal, but you wouldn't like to say definitely?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. That would be what I were saying. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In some places at that time men felt they risked losing their job or th
eir house if they voted differently from their employers. Do you know if your father felt himself under that kind of pressure to vote for a particular party?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. His home and his house had nothing to do with him employers - ever, at any time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about his employers, they never tried to bring any pressure to bear on him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Not that I ever remember. He - he was - well I think I told you, he was - a bit what we called a boss's man, because he thought - that they had the education and the abili
ty - to govern and to rule. But there was no pressure, I'm quite sure there was no pressure anywhere. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
scales it was?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember whether your father was a member of the Conservative party or not
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think not. No, I - I think he was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember him ever working for one of the parties at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, he wasn't that kind of man. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you wouldn't remember either of your parents taking any part in political activities other than at election times?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No. No, this was talked about in the home - at election times, they didn't - go to - I hardly think they went to any public meeting, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They just actually voted?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When your parents were not doing their work how did they spend their spare time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well - father had poultry. And he spent a lot of his spare time - amongst the poultry. My mother didn't go out much. You see she was - no, she'd got - had this - youngest sister, in her forties and 
- she had a weak heart rather, she couldn't do strenuous things, she did her housework but as a rule she would sit down and put her feet up afterwards. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That was as much as she could cope with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. She'd - well, very occasionally she went to visit relatives but - normally she was a stay at home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother have any interests outside the home at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well she had the little business you see. Which was an interest, that was - hers you know. Hers plus one of us helping her. And 
she would - was the - managing person.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When did you buy the little shop, the first one?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
19 - late in 19 - 02. Yes. It was September or October and it would be - she'd always wanted it. She wanted it and she'd never been able to have it. And - it
 was only a little shop but - it became - available through - somebody else's illness, and so she wanted to take it on.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you don't remember her ever going out to enjoy herself?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She went to the anniversary at the chapel, if her feet were good 
enough. You see her feet swelled up quite a lot. Well it stopped her from a lot. She went - went to - visit her - relatives, she had the mother - down Lowcombe and she went to see her and some sisters. And - and her brother who is - father - the one I'm g
oing to Morecambe with, it was a little - clan of the family down there in Morecambe and we lived at Beechcliffe, and so it wasn't too far. She went to visit them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would she usually go by herself or would she usually take one of you with her?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh she'd go by herself. Yes. If she wasn't able to go by herself she wouldn't be going, you see. If she felt well enough she'd go.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When did your father get home form work in the evenings when he was at Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 scale?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Round six. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How many evenings a week would be spent at home? Would it be every night?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh - yes, all of them, he - he didn't go out. No, he wasn't - he wasn't one to go out at all.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He never attended any}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 clubs or pubs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, when - when we were very young - I think 
he went - that was from Long Lee into the town - I'm telling you now what mother told us, and mother pointed out the fact to him that three children and another on the way, there wouldn't be any money for beer. And - yes, it stopped, he never went any mor
e. His - his children came - before anything else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He'd only been a mild drinker?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh yes, oh yes, only a mild drinker, but - if they got a group of them you see it was one with me and one with me, and - just like it could be nowadays, no differen
t and - it was - it - wouldn't have been much money then, but proportionate to the income it was. Money that couldn't be spared.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So your mother would never go with him?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no. No. Yes, they - they didn't ever leave us. No. No they didn't, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your father take part in any sport at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I don't think so. He had his hens. Always his interest, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did he attend the races?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did he ever have a bet?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No. No. Definitely against that. Yes. Definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother or father belong to any saving clubs? At that time there were such things as boot clubs, sick clubs, funeral clubs.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh they - they might - me mother would have done. My mother would have done something like that. I remember her havin
g tickets to spend - at Halsome}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
s, she went and had - tickets with tea and saved them up and spent them, and - there - there was something in the way of a savings club, she went to buy us shoes and things, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Shoe club kind of thing?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Tha
t's right. Yes, that's right and - went - she would be paying first, she wouldn't get the goods. Pay so much and - that's right, or nearly the end and pay the balance. Yes, I don't think there were ever any - debts. No, I don't think so. Yes, paid their w
ay. There was - a little insurance paid. Yes, on us. A small one. Penny or tuppence a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That would be in case of death?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, it was death - in my young days. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't get anything for sickness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think there'd be something f
or sickness - connected with my father's work. I've a feeling that there was - something there that was a sort of safeguard. Wouldn't be much but it might be a little bit - not - out of his wage by agreement. Yes. Yes. There wouldn't be anything more than
 that, be - something small like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How did you get on with your brother and sisters?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Really - the one sister next to me - I'm afraid we were very opposites and - we did quite a bit of - quarrelling, the two of us, simply because we were oppos
ites. You know, but there was nothing - serious about it. I mean if - well we - she'd get a bit of a bump from father or mother, my mother in particular if - if it wasn't settled up in a bit, quick you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about your brother, did you get on all right with him?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes, on the whole. He - he wasn't a one brother with sisters and - I think he always liked to feel that but he was - sort of - slightly better, yes, in those days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Your two youngest sisters really wouldn't come into it would they because they'd be so much younger than you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No. Well the one one was seven years younger, the other was sixteen years younger than me, I was - nearly a young woman - when the youngest one was born you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Even the one seven years younger than you.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well I was - I was the big sister and - yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was there one you felt particularly close to?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The youngest, but you see that comes after doesn't it? Well it wold still be the youngest.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It would still be before 1919 though wouldn't it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh yes, 1919, I was twenty-nine. Yes, I - I'd be the closest to the youngest and the next closest to the next, and the least closest to the one that was nearest. Mm. It's simply because we were different in - temperament altogether
 and outlook and everything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 As a child who did you play with, your brother or your sister or neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Neighbours children. We played in a gang, being a place like Long Lee, as it was then, you see, smaller than it is now, and - in s
ummer - we were out of doors and we played as a gang. A - a few neighbours children and - and the rest of - we might at one time have been a bit nearer to so and so's children and - and have a fortnight we'd nearer to those and not so friendly with those 
but - there was never anything - no serious quarrels you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It would mainly be neighbours children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You varied between a number of them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Where did you play, in the yard or in a garden or in the street or in other homes
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
It was the road. You couldn't call it a street because there were only houses - it was a - you know, if you can go up Long Lee now, there's a junction of the roads, one to Harden and one off past a little chapel, well we played in that V,
 but there was no traffic. We just played in that V and sometimes we went over to the - over the wall into the field. Nobody said anything.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 LongLee is still comparatively rural?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Pret - pretty much the same I - I had a ride over there a few years
 ago, and - all the things I remembered were still there. There were still the odd houses built in among, well quite a few, but the things I remembered were still there because - the man who was driving it, it was the ambulance you know, I'd been to Bradf
o
rd, and - I - oh that house, yes. Some - yes, some friends of mine lived there or so and so lived - oh yes, that hasn't altered. I was talking like that you see, and then he said, how long is that since? And - I came up with a jolt, I said seventy years. 
Which it was, it was only this last - spring you see, was that when I'd been to Bradford and they sent the ambulance for me. Had to come back in it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It would be surrounded by fields?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't play in the fields at all, it was always in the roadway?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
The one opposite to our house, we played in because nobody objected. But it did belong to somebody. But the other fields we didn't play in - on the other side of the road - I think they grew - grass in them for meadows for cutting
. Well the children hadn't to play in them, it would spoil the grass you see. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you'd play in the road or in this particular field?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Yes. And - if we went a little father up - the road there was a little moor-. And we played 
on that. Yes? Yes, in the summer. Yes. And that - well as we grew older we went up the bigger moor, the one that extends over to Hubbalds you know, but there was a little bit of moor, I think it's still there - up above that, well above the then houses, y
ou know, there some built all the way up. A little bit of moor with a quarry in.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And that would all be common land?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. And father had his hens up there, only - only they were over a wall or otherwise - one time he had a - a wire netting fe
nce and then he got a piece over the wall and - that pleased him better over the wall. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What games did you play at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Skipping - and cheques. Do you know what cheques is?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 Is that sort of hopsc}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 otch?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No - little square chin
a things, you threw a little china ball up and picked one up and caught the ball again. And - now down by my - down at Nelson's Place they called it Jacks. They played it with pebbles. We bought these things in a shop for - ha'penny and a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And were they numbered?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No, no, they weren't numbered, different colours. Might be different colours. But your tawas we called it, which was the large marble - and you threw it up, that would bounce - if you had it on flags, I don't know that it bounced v
ery well on earth, on the earthen road. It was earth road you know, it wasn't tarmac. Not then. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And you called it a taw?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 A taw. Taw. Taw. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That was the little ball that you threw up?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That we threw up and - and - you threw it
 and caught one cheque and caught the ball. Threw it again and caught two until you - you were very clever if you could throw it up and scoop all the four and catch the ball before it bounced. You allowed it to bounce when you were - learning as it was, b
u
t you got more clever it didn't have to bounce, you did it very - very quickly, mm. And the boys played with - smaller marbles which - they also called taws. Little ones, half an inch. But that was a different game, that was - thumbing the - one against t
he other.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you allowed to get dirty when you played out?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, a bit. Yes. So long as we got washed when we came in. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were you free to play with any one you pleased?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. If we fell out it was our own - affair, we fell out and stayed out or make friends. Mother never interfered. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So your parents never discouraged you from playing with certain children?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, I don't think so, not particularly. Some were a bit cleaner than other. Some were a bit poorer than others. But -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But the poorer ones you were never discouraged from playing with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh no, no, we went to - into their houses, you know, if - calling for them as we - you know, or go and see if they were ready. Was who we felt like going with at the moment. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you belong to any youth organisations at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Only the - Sunday school and the Band of Hope. There wasn't anything else. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I should like to ask you now about how you spent your free time when you were at school, did you have any hobbies then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
I liked to draw. But I loved to read, I spent every spare minute - I could reading. You know, mother'd stop me at times because - she thought I - I read too much. And - if I could get hold of anything to read it didn't mat
ter what it was. Yes, I'd sit and read.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you have any pets?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 A little dog sometimes. And always a cat.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would it be your dog?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh it would belong to the household, it would be most likely me brother's. I think we only had one at Long 
Lee, we had some more after we went to Beechcliffe but we - never more than one. But - oftentimes there was a dog, a little terrier or - or something of that kind, often a stray, one time we had a stray definitely. And cats were often strays that stayed i
n. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever collect anything, such as cigarette cards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
I don't think there were any. No, me mother collected soup coup - salt - coupons, but I don't really thing there was anything for us to collect. I don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember ever doing any gardening at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We didn't have a garden.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever go fishing, with your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh - no - there were nowhere to fish. I - I caught a little fish so big in a - in a well. Scooped it up and took it home in my hand. Mm
. Come down the drain, mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already told me you went up on the moors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you go for walks with your friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes - when we were - reasonably old enough. We felt quite safe up }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 
there. There was no - thou shall}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180  not about i
t you know. Although if went - on as far as Druids Altar - you know where that is - well - in the summer holidays we might go and there. But if we were - if we were very late home at teatime we got scolded for going - so far away, you see. But the nearer 
moors we were not - oh and it was mind the quarries. You see, mind the quarries, because they were open -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were they worked at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They weren't redundant then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. No, no, they weren't redundant, they were worked.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you did quite a bit of walking?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, we did a lot of walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever have a bicycle?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. I - I wanted one when I was fifteen but you see that goes far back, I - I couldn't get to have a bicycle.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you take part in any sports when you were younger?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Not very much. At - when it was the Sunday school - what did we call it - Whitsuntide, Whitsuntide - at Whit Monday - well we'd been races then, we'd do things like that but - we didn't have - bats and balls to play cricket. Some of the boys might.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But not the girls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. There wasn't one in our house. I don't remember. If there was me dad would have to make it but - I sort of don't remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you go to any theatres at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Never. You had to b
e in Keighley you see. And we - and me mother couldn't - there was - there was me - me and younger ones you see and - there was no time and I don't think there was any money for theatres.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Or concerts or music halls?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Sunday concerts, that was all, nothing - nothing on a bigger way at all. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would they be at the church, the Sunday concerts?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Little chapel. Oh Sunday concerts, no. There wouldn't be any Sunday concerts. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever go to the music hall?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever go to the cinema?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
They weren't there. No. No. The - when we were - children at school we used to get little tickets given at the gates, to take home - and - if you - had that ticket and it came on Saturday afternoon you could go in for a penny. It
 was the beginnings of pictures. But mother flatly refused. She'd known cases where there'd been a fire and lots of little children had been - burnt and - or killed, every - you cannot go. Not there. So - there was absolutely nothing up to my being - thir
teen of that kind at all. But aft - because of the risks and the dangers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your parents give you any pocket money when you were still at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Ha'penny - ha'penny every Friday night. And when we got to be about ten it was a penny.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What would you spend it on?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Sweets. Nearly always sweets. Or a book when it got to be a penny. Yes. After I was about - ten or eleven - there was a - once a fortnight a visit to my father's relatives - at Silsden. And we'd be given - the railway fare
, it had to be down to the railway station and go on the train, and the railway fare and a penny perhaps. And we sometimes got another penny given to come home with. The railway return ticket you see we'd to go, but - Uncle - Uncle Jack gave us a - a less
o
n on this - he had a - a bit larger organ, he - he was very musical was Uncle Jack, and he was self-taught. He was very musical. He was a clipper. And - he gave us a little lesson and that's how we learnt to play the - little old harmonium that we had at 
home you see.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did anyone outside the home help your mother look after the house or family? Such as perhaps a sister?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 If she was ill, the same as when she was having the - child who was seven years younger than me - an auntie would come, or grand
mother would come. And - you know, see her through. Help her.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What sort of things would they do for her, would they clean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh they - if - they'd cook and - yes, the house'd be kept just the same as she would keep it. I mean we would have to scho
ol, at that time they might have given us something to take and not come home at dinner time, that could be possible - for a few days or a week. But - I can remember grandma being there and she'd - mostly do some sewing as well, whilst she was there, help
 mother to make some of the - clothes for us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She never had any regular help?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was just when she was in bed?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Y-s. That's right. There wasn't - yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember when your mother was ill or confined to bed how she managed, you said your grandma or aunties came?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember what happened when one of your younger sisters was born? Did a doctor come or a midwife?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Doctor. Yes, somebody - a neighbour's - we were put to bed out of the way you see. The
 baby would be born downstairs, 'cos there was only one bedroom. We - I remember us being put to bed, and - a neighbour's son - was sent - to run to Keighley, to get the doctor, to - run mostly - it was downhill you know and - a big strong - youth he woul
d be then, and he had to run and every doctor came up with this horse and trap, you see, no motor cars. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did she have the baby on a settee or something downstairs?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right, I - I just don't know, I mean - they weren't old enough, I was o
nly - she was seven years younger than me, well I was seven wasn't I. I cannot tell you how they managed. They'd bring her to bed afterwards. Because I can remember somebody having a struggle up to light the bedroom fire, and it was found out that it had 
been blocked up previously, the - that - that's why I can remember it, the place was full of smoke and it was quite a - quite a commotion for the time being.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And when the second girl was born you'd be getting older, you'd be sixteen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, I w
as sixteen. Well - an auntie came then and grandmother, grandmother was still - on the go. And - she had her upstairs in the bedroom, yes, I was downstairs at the time. I know they told me - I'd got another baby sister. Later on. I got to know. I hadn't g
ot to know all there as to know about it but I - I knew - that mother was gong to have this baby, I knew where it came from. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your parents have any relatives living nearby when they were at Long Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, they were down in Lawcombe in the town, there were no relatives - nearby.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How much did you see of them? You said your mother used to go and visit them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes - they came up sometimes. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Every week or every month?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no, well it would be irregular, because yo
u see they would come up in summer and they wouldn't come up in winter because it was a long walk. If the weather was bad.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But your mother would go and see them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well she had to go in the town for shopping. That was necessary. After or before. Y
ou could shop until midnight in the town then, you know, so she'd go and visit grandmother, well sometimes - because she took one of us with her I think as I've told you to help to carry the things home, and - we'd go up to grandma's and - one of the aunt
ies perhaps be coming up in the town as well, they'd have a shop round together you know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your parents have any friends? Friends who they would visit?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, mot - not a lot, but we had some friends at Steeton, who had lived at Keighley, t
hey'd lived in Park Lane, and the man was a gardener. And when he - he went to Alec Healey's, you know - of Alec Healey, a great photographer, yes, he has exhibit - well he's dead now but - his work is still exhibited, he was a - an outstanding photograph
er}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 , and he had a nice house at St}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
eeton, and we were taken there, when the - people of the house were away - and then we could go round the gardens. It was very much touch me not but - it was - it's sort of an education in a way. And after - have tea at thei
r little house which was just outside the - the grounds, yes, like - it - it wasn't exactly a lodge but - they were in that position, they could have kept an eye out and stopped anybody going there who should not have gone. And we were taken.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would they come and visit your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Occasionally they'd come and visit us at Long Lee. And they had children about the same age as us you see. Mm, yes, we all got on together.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say then that they shared the same friends or did your mother have friend of her own and your father have friends of his own?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well, this - they mostly shared them, father had a few friends he worked with. And they - they paid us - always one annual visit on Christmas Day morning, father's friends, yes. If they 
were walking by they'd knock at the door and come and - call and pass half an hour on or something. But -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It wouldn't be any prearranged visit or anything?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, there wasn't - there wasn't much in the way of prearranged visits.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would your father go and visit them, at their homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I don't know. Just don't know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But your mother didn't have any friends of her own?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, she - she got - friendly with neighbours - around, because one of the neighbours was there when - when this 
baby was born, as well as auntie and - and grandma, I know one of the - I remember one of the neighbours being there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you say that friends were invited into the house, these people from Steeton for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They used to come and have a meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh - they came, yes, they did.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And your father's friends used to come and pop in?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Mm. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How often would you have visitors of this kind? Would it be fairly frequently?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh - at any time, they just came. I mean somet
imes it might have been by invitation. But - quite often - if they turned up well there was always enough food. You know, it would be simple perhaps but - there's always enough -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It wouldn't be every week that you'd have visitors?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not quite every week, but - yes. Three or - every third or fourth week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You said they'd be offered something to eat and drink?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was there any particular day or occasions when you'd exchange visits, when people would visit you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't t
hink so. No. No. No, there'd be perhaps a letter sent or - or perhaps - if one had come to see it would be, now you come to ours so and so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say that the friends invited into the home were friends of both your mother and father?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Or
 they became so, were accepted as friends of both. Yes, I mean if these friends of father's turned up - mother wasn't at all against them, it was an open door, come in, you see. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were there friends who came in casually without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There - there'd be some, yes, the men, it's just that I can't just remember anybody else.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would neighbours pop in without an invitation?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, but not - not for a meal, as a rule. You see we lived so near together, they'd - they'd come in - w
ell if one hadn't been so well - so see how they were, the - you know, Mrs so and so said you weren't so well, I've come to see you and - and - vica versa if - you know, I mean the children would carry that many a time, the children would say - my man's n
ot so well, and my mam's poorly and then - the other mam'd - go to see her, 'cos - it wasn't much more than a stone's throw all the lot at Long Lee at that time.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So they would just pop in for a chat?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already told me that your parents went out visiting these friends at Steeton for instance?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. And of course - the relatives. Very occasionally to me father's relatives at Steeton. At Silsden, but you see that involved - a bigger journey, down to the railway station, a rail journey, and an expense if they had to take two or three of us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
People often tell us that in those days they made their own amusements, what do you think your parents did when they got together with their friends? Or neighbours? Would they make music or have games or just sit around and talk?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
I think they'd just sit around and talk. I mean if me aunties came to our house, the harmonium got going. But - when we went to somebody else's house - well there only was the - music at me f
ather's folks and we didn't go there very often. And in any case he - he taught music and could just as easily have - have had a - a pupil coming, in which case we - trotted to the next - there were two or three fairly near together you see and - if he wa
s having a pupil we out and went into one of the other houses. It was nearly all conversation there, there was much - playing of games.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Many people divide society into different social classes or groups. In that time before 1918 did you think of some b
elonging to one and some to another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well we knew a few people who were definitely richer than us.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What would you call them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Just say well off. Well off, yes, that was most often the - the word that we used.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about the people like yourself, what would you call those?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh just friends, you didn't call them anything. Well working people, we all worked for a wage. Yes. Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You can't think of anymore other than the better off and the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not - not in those years, not up there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already said that you thought of yourself as being part of the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What sort of people belonged to the same class or group as yourself?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you mean what sort of work did th
ey do? Well there - there were some friends we had - because there was a boy me brother's age and a girl my age you know, equivalent nearly to us, and they kept the little house at the chapel, they were the chapel keepers, and - their father I think worke
d
 in a flour mill. Down at Low Bridge, and I'm pretty sure he worked in a flour mill - there. And - some other friends we had they had a little farm. So their father ran the little farm, you see. They had quite a family of those. And - well I had some more
 school friends and their father worked in the town but I don't know what he did. Probably worked in one of the black shops there'd be at that time. Some of me uncles and cousins worked in - Prince Smith's you know -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In a sort of foundry?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Foundry workers. There'd be a few who would be foundry workers.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So they'd be sort of engineers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. A mixture.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And the farmer that you knew wasn't a sort of gentleman farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no. Oh no. He -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He was a working farmer?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, he -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Who didn't have much more money to go out than you people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
That's right, he did a bit of trading sometimes, you know, and made a few extra pounds that way. They didn't lack anything although they'd seven children, so - he managed to make a living for them one way or another.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What sort of people would you say belonged to the other class, the better off class.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Better off class. Yes. Well - there was one man - that lived at Long Lee - and - it was well known in Keighley at that time 
because he was the Mayor one time. They called him Harry Longsden. Mr Longsden, he belonged to the Church of England, and - he was - the gentleman of the district, but he really married one of the Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 scales and he worked in the office, where me father 
worked in the workshop, he worked in the office there you see. So he was definitely what you'd call - the gentleman of Long Lee. Well he was the first to - he - had a coachman and - an open - carriage you see, well it - it happen be closed in winter and o
p
en in summer, but my father was - friendly with his coachman, that was one of his man friends. And - they were the first to have a motor car, the first motor car I ever saw. Up there. It belonged to them. And of course he had two sons and I daresay it was
 the - sons who had wanted the motor car. They worked in the - office work. I don't think they all worked at Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
scales, that I couldn't say. They father did, he was the - my father's director. He was a director, he'd married a Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
scale you see. Yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So he wasn't just an office worker, he was actually a director of the company?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Can you remember being brought up to treat people of one sort differently from people of another?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well we were more shy with those. We did
n't - bow to them or anything like that. But if they smiled at us we smiled back shyly. We didn't - we never encroached if you know what I mean.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But your parents never said that you'd to -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were never told to curtsey or show respect in some way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh no. Oh no. Oh not that kind of thing, no. I mean we belonged to the village, they didn't - own us in any shape or form, and - it isn't - it wasn't like living on an estate, you know, although they had carriage - went to and fro on 
the road and we - just scattered a bit if we were playing you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was there anyone you called sir or madam?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember anyone showing respect to your parents in any of these ways?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, no, I don't think so. They were pretty much all of them on a - on a level. You know.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In the village who were considered the most important people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, it's - that's right - Longsden, Longsden, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He was considered the most important person?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, he was considered th
e wealthiest at that time, mind there was a - another family, a large family they called Faulds's, well - they lived a little bit lower towards Keighley, but they - they more or less ran the little chapel and the Sunday school, they were important there, 
you see, the - but - one would be }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 superintendent}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
 and another would be a teacher and - they - the little functions and everything - they - they did the managing as you might say, of them.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They were considered important as well in the village were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well - yes - they were - they were in between though, and nearer to us, we - I was invited to their houses sometimes, but it would be if they were getting up something and they wanted you to - well - let them hear you say your recitation before the n
ight, that kind of thing you see. And train a - train a few little singers and make the - little bits of fancy dress for them, you know, they would what we call get it up - in these days.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So it was through the chapel that you came into contact with these people called Faulds?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever come into contact with the family of Harry Longsen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Why would you say that they were considered important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well they lived in a bigger house, and they had th
e - carriage and pair, you see, and the coachman. And nobody else had anything like that there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was outward appear}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 ances that made people consider}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180  them important?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It wasn't the way they behaved?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was there possessions which created this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The shopkeepers up at Long Lee, who would you say they associated with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There weren't any. Little sweet shop, that was all. And -
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And the people who owned that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well the two elderly ladie
s and they said yes luv and - that sort of thing, you went in for a ha'penny worth of sweets, I presume to the other people they were just neighbours. You didn't - did-'t set them apart in any way, we had a ha'penny we used to call on our way down to scho
ol and - spend it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about the clergy, who were they friends with would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well you see there weren't any really, it was a little chapel, there'd just be a local preacher come and - and take a service on a Sunday, there wasn't - there wasn't a belonging minister, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about the teachers at the school, who would you say they were friends with?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well we'd to go down to Parkwood School. Wasn't a school at Long Lee, there wasn't - it wasn't there, no, we had to go to Parkwood Sc
hool. Well those teachers lived anywhere in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you wouldn't know anything about their life outside?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, not outside school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already told me that the farmer you knew was a friend with you, with your family, they weren't part
icularly friends with other farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
All - all the children were all friends together you see, there were seven of them. Over the ages, and - and - there were four of us, and three more or four of the little family at the chapel house and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were just telling em that the farmers around Long Lee were working farmers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And were friends with the people in the village really?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And you played with their children. Now about employers, it looks as it at that time the only
 employer you knew was this Harry Longsden, who was a director of Summer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 scales?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Who would you say the Longsden family associated with, who were their friends?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I don't know. No idea. No, I've no idea, not their private life. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What sort of people would you say went to the church?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The chapel? That we went to.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, the church, Church of England?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well the Church of England church was just over Thaites Brow, we didn't go, but this farmer's children did. So the farme
r evidently, or the mother, wanted her children to go to church of England, and of course some of the - people who live over - what we used to call over the b}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 r}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ow - would go to the church.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So it would be a fairly cross section of the population would you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It wasn't either wealthy people or poorer people?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, oh no, no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about the chapel, what sort of people went to the chapel with you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well these - this family they called Faulds was quite a
 big family. And - and they'd been one big family and then - one of the son's had had a big family so they're like a lot in the two - there are a lot of them altogether, and - they were the main string - of the chapel, actually, as I told you, they - arra
nging things and one of them would be secretary or something like that, be responsible for - getting the preachers each week. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would there be quite a lot of people just like yourselves?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. And - I'll tell you who went to the chapel wh
o was fairly influential, a family called Woolands - Woolards, only the said Woolard in those days, it's Woolard, and - there's some of those in Keighley yet. Yes. And - they - they - well one of those was the chapel - choirmaster, keep - having a little 
choir - there yo}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 u see and - being a superintende}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
nt and sometimes, they'd be on an equal footing with the Faulds but there wouldn't be as many of them. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Where you lived up at Long Lee did all the people in the working class have the same standard of 
living, or would you say there were different groups within the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
They - they mostly had the same standard. I don't remember many others going out to work. I don't remember, there might have been, but if - if there was any higher standin
g than another it was - whose mother was a good baker and whose mother wasn't such a good baker, and it made for quite a difference in the - standard of living, in those days. You know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The standard of the meals you mean?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Yes, if we went to some of our friends sometimes - there wasn't - quite as good a provision put on the table. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You can't remember in the working class at Long Lee there being a family who were say considerably poorer than your family can you?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, t
here was one or two. Yes, there was one or two, well - they - they wouldn't - well there - there was one - I remember going to one house one time, and - I think - I think the father must have gone and left, I - I don't - distinctly remember anything only 
h
er mother, and - you see if you went with - another child to their house, they generally - gave you something - to eat because it would be perhaps from school and it wasn't quite time for your - proper tea. And - that was the only place where I had - brea
d
 dipped in milk and then dipped in sugar and then given to eat. You know I - there was nothing else to put on the bread you see. At - at least I considered there was nothing else. When it was accepted by those children and - therefore accepted by us you k
n
ow. And - there was that slight difference and there was another family - where unfortunately the husband had to be in prison for something, or one of the - big brothers, I don't quite remember but - somebody in that family had to be in prison, whether it
 was for - theft or what I'm not sure. Well that family's standard was - reduced for the time being, you know. So there were some families who were decidedly poorer than us. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say that there were some families in the village who were thought of as being rough and others as being respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well it applied to these, particularly the }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 
one - where there was one in pr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 i}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 s}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 on. They were -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They were thought of by the other working people as being rough were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. As being - yes, as being rougher. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were there any thought of as being particularly respectable?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. Well - yes, the chapel keepers family were. Definitely. And I think we were. We were always clean and we were always well behaved and we were always well fed. And of course the farmer's family were.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember a distinction of this kind, of being rough and respectable, between craftsmen and labourers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so. They considered him - either more fortunate or better off if he was 
a craftsman. But - it didn't make any different to the - friendship between them - that I remember.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your mother and father have the same attitude to people in different classes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, I think so, you see my mother had been in service when she
 was young, and me father of course - like respected the people who were above him, well of course - put it that way.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So they were both like this were they?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, they're both - not strongly so but - yes, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you think your mother saw herself as belonging to a particular social class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so. No, as just a wife and mother.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She didn't se it in any other way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was it possible at that time to move from one class to another, and can you remember anyone who did this?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Not definitely. I mean - if - if such a thing happened that - because one's father had a bit better job than another - some of them went to the grammar schools. Well they were on the way to getting into a - better position. But it - it wasn't notic}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 e}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 able up to me being thirteen. You see, and then I moved so I didn't see the effects of it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember anyone being described to you as a real gentleman or a real lady?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember seeing a policeman around Long Lee when you were a child?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, there wasn't one resident up there. It was - I daresay a case of - if anybody did anything bad we'll get the police -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But there wasn't one there?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, there might have been one over Thwaites Brow, but I couldn't be sure.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You don't remember regularly seeing a policeman around where you lived?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember ever when you were naught}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6905885\charrsid15471180 y being threaten}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ed by your mother saying I'll call the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Not - no - mother said I will - I - she didn't say I'll give you a good h}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ding but - I'll - I don't know, I've forgotten what she did say. It was on your bottom you got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She never threatened you with the policeman?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was your home rented at Long Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you see anything of your landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No. Father paid the rent - in town, yes, it was rented I remember him - telling my mother - when we were going to come there, that he could get this house - for three shillings a week.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you didn't know anything about the landlord?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No. He - he paid the rent somewhere in town before he came home.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you remember feeling that your parents had to struggle to make ends meet when you were little?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well we knew so. It wasn't - it wasn't made upsetting to us. It was a case of - we can't afford it so that's that and - and that was it you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What did you think about this at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Nothing. Every - all the other families were pretty much the same.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was your father ever ill or out of work at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was before you were born?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. When he had that accident and was out of work, he was never out of work to my knowledge - afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When there was someone
 in the district whom the people disapproved of very strongly, was there any special way in which they showed it? Do you remember anyone being made to leave by rough music?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 To what - did you say?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In some parts of the country if there was a famil
y who were thought of as being particularly rough, perhaps the father was continually drink, or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The people in the neighbourhood would show this by playing what they called rough music in that they would stand outside th
e house and bang pans together and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Mm. I don't know anything about anything like that. No. I thought you said rough usage. That's - that's why I said what. No, it's a new one to me, I've never heard of that. No. No. No, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So 
you don't remember anyone being dealt with in a certain way, you don't remember a man who was perhaps unkind to his family being ostracised, in any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think - no, I think perhaps - I'm not sure - perhaps - the other men - would go and have a talk
 to them. If there was such a thing. I - I don't remember any great distress - amongst them, I know some of the children as you say - didn't have the same to eat, that we did, but - I don't remember any being - very badly treated. They weren't knocked abo
ut or cruelly treated, not up Long Lee. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you go straight to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Your parents didn't give you any lessons ever, did they ever teach you to read or anything before you went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 They bought us little picture books a
nd I think one or the other of them would - read a bit to us or tell us what the pictures were - before - I had a picture book - all birds. No, teacher gave me that at school, I brought that home. I can't remember what we had before, but we - if you got a
 little bit too big for a doll there'd be a picture book instead of a doll, you know.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you never had any set lessons at home with your parents?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so, it would be - a case of come and sit down and be quiet and I'll read to you perhaps.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How old were you when you first went to school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Just five.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What was the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Parkwood. Parkwood Street. Remember - yes, Parkwood is all one word, and it's Parkwood Street school. The - the wood is the wood you see and - Pa
rkwood Street was the road - a long road all the way along. It had been originally all along the bottom of Park Wood, that it - got the - and then the houses built and it was called Parkwood Street.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were five when you went?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you first started what time of the day did you go and when did you come back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
We - went at nine o'clock, I can remember being taken, I remember my mother taking me to school the first time. And - so far as I know I had to walk home at dinnertime. But t
he other children would be - we'd all be going in a group you see, but it was the infants school that I went to, the farther on of the two schools. They're still there are those schools.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There's Parkwood Junior and Parkwood Infants.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It would be Parkwood Infants and sort of Junior and Secondary school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right, yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You finished at lunchtime, what time did you finish in the afternoon?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think it was quarter past four. You see we had a long lunch ti
me. We went back at quarter to two and I think it was quarter past - four, when we came out. And we all came home - together.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you started school at first when you were five you went to both morning and afternoon school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't go half time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, no, because it was all - when you went you went.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What kind of school was it, was it a church school or a board school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, it was a board school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And it was a day school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There were no boarders?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was a day school and it was a mixed school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You used to walk to school every day?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How long did it take you to get there from Long Lee?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Twenty or twenty-five minutes. It's downhill. Yes. It took longer to walk home, uphill, you wanted at least half an hour - to go up. Yes.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The first morning your mother took you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And after that who took you then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Nobody, we went - a group. Everybody about the same age.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Your brother would be there?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
He might, but - me brother would be with the boys. It'd be - it'd be look round for the other children who had been going a few months longer than me. There were quite a group of us all in the same year.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And you went home for your midday meal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What did you think of school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh I liked it. Oh I liked school. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What did you think about the teachers?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I loved them. There were - there were fine. There was a Miss Brant who was the headmis
tress, and I forget what they called the teacher who did - separate class, there were four separate classes, under this headmistress. But I liked school, I liked everything belonging to it. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 Did the teachers emphasiz}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 e certain things as importa
nt in life, such as manners? Were they particular about these things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well, not in the infants school, they might have done in the bigger school after.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about tidiness?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I'll talk about your whole school life, they were particular about manners later?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about tidiness, were they particular about that?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes, you had to be tidy. This was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What did they say if you went to school with dirty hands or dirty boots?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You - well - I
 was fortunate in that, I daresay, because my mother insisted we went with clean clogs, we'd to learn to clean them ourselves, so I - I wasn't ever in trouble over it. But one girl who was - was stood out in the - main entrance door with a tin of blacking
 and some brushes and told to get on with it. But tat would be - she'd be - perhaps - nine or something like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about punctuality, did they insist on you being there on time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about ways of speaking? Were you ever corrected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well - not unless you talked very broad. I think you were - you were kindly led you see, we did talk broad - because we all talked broad together. But I think we were more kindly led, perhaps - scoffed at a bit, it depended on the teache
r, there were - some teachers kinder than other teachers, they varied.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 If you did something the teachers disapproved of what would happen?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh hold your hand out and get the cane. Yes, definitely.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Girls as well as boys?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. You might get a one - one or two warnings but if you ignored those warnings - you did, you got it.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What sort of offences would you get the cane for?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Talking. And you had been warned not to. Yes, and you continued. And of course bad work sometimes. Yes, yo
u could - you could get caned if - if you were getting your sums wrong - continually or bad writing or things like that. It was a punishment. Yes, was punished then.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did your parents show an interest in your school work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes, they did. E
specially if we - were told to take some home and show our parents, which we sometimes were. Oh yes, they were very interested. And of course sometimes - school books were bought, you could buy them in Marks and Spencer}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 
\insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 \rquote }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 s for a penny or tuppence at the most. And sometimes in the Saturday night sho}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 p}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ping - a book would be included, see, writing and - at home, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And they would help you at home?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Well they'd commend you if you did it properly you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So did they ask you what you did at school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh I daresay, yes, fairly often that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did they ever visit the school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
I - yes. I - I think - I think mother only visited the school if we were away because we were ill. So that it wasn't just a scrap of paper sent with another child
. Think she'd make it in her way to go - I once had - some trouble with my eyes for a week or two, and I would think - think she went then to - to tell the teacher that I couldn't possibly come - to the school.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did she ever go to school to see the teachers, to discuss you with them?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
She - she did but it might have been because she went on one errand and - and because she knew - she knew - the teacher that told her about how I was going on at sometimes and so - I don't think she went on purpose for that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did the other children come from similar types of home to your own or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Those from Long Lee did. But there were a lot from round - round the Parkwood area who had not - anything nearly so good homes as we had.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Came from much poorer homes?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes, much poorer. 'Cos occasionally - well occasionally I was taken with one girl - to her home and it shocked me very decidedly and I went home and told my mother what - what it was like, but that was another home where - there was a non 
existent father, you see, and - you see in those days - the mother's simply had to go out and get what work she could if the father had deserted her. And she'd these two children and it was a - a very very poor home indeed. But there you are.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did the teachers single out some children for different treatment from the others?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not - not unless they were obstinate children, bad - really bad mannered children.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were there any gangs or groups in the school? For instance, was there a Long Lee gang?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well I - I think there was to some extent. Yes, I think there was.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Were there any children who were left out of things?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not altogether but - there might have been sometimes for instance there was one - little scandal, one - one girl arrive
d with gifts for everybody, in the class. This is for you, this if for you, this is for you. And - it was something most unusual - and she'd been stealing. And then treating her - you know - yes, yes, yes, that's right, yes, she was, she wanted to - be th
e
 generous person you see in the class. And - of course - well we took ours home at dinnertime you know and my mother says, where have you got that from? And - oh the - so and so, I forget what they called the girl, so and so, this girl had been - she'd gi
v
en us all some, you see, I had - I think I had a few chalks in a - little box, she'd given us all something and mother says, well you just take them back. She said, I'm sure that little girl - shouldn't have been giving them, you see, as soon as we said s
h
e'd given all some, you see, to me mother's mind was where did that money come from. And - I think a few of us were arriving back in the afternoon with these things, and then - the teacher found out, she perhaps - heard some whispers or saw some of it - c
h
anging hands, I don't remember but the - the teacher had the girl out in front of the class and gave her - quite a lecture about it. And of course she admitted you see what she'd done. And - I think for the little well - while that girl - suffered, being 
cut out for a bit.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Then she was accepted back?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, yes, it didn't last but - it did happen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't go to another school did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You continued at Parkwood?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. When I left I left from - when we went - when we went to Beechcliffe.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How old were you when you left school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Thirteen. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you have stayed on longer if you'd have the opportunity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes. I liked - well - I - I didn't break me heart over it. Because I was willing to 
accept anything life was bringing I think. I think I'd that sort - I didn't break my heart over it at all. But if it had been my lot to have gone on to school I should have gone on quite cheerfully and - yes, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you attend any part time education afterwards?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, I went to night school, at Utley.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What did you take?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Dressmaking and cookery, on a modified scale, I made myself some }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 \endash 
}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180  a}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
summer frock mostly by hand, you know, in brown linen - what my mother thought I ought to have at that time. And - of course there's cookery class was - little bits of pies and things like that which we could carry home afterwards.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How long did you go for?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I think only the one winter. Yes. To evening classes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So would you say that you have regrets about your education or not?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No, not really. I mean it's no good regretting it in later life if you didn't regret it at the time. Well you see, I - my life changed altogether, I went to a new Sunday school and made new friends and - and 
my horizons widened out quite a lot. Because one of these - friends had to be in the shop}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180  }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
with her mother and I had to be in the shop with my mother and - and the chapel was bigger and the? Sunday school was bigger and - there was -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You made a whole new circle of friends?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So it was quite an adventure for you, just leaving school and taking a job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, it - that's right. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you think you benefited from attending school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh yes, I think so. Well - I don
't know - how long it is since I went - oh I went to the chemists that's right, for something and you see as I'm older like I don't have to pay for them you know, 'cos he brought me a - he brought me a paper and - would I sign this paper. And - mind I'm a
 
- I'm a fairly good writer, for an old person you see and - of course I wrote my name quite quickly, 'cos I did a lot of writing in shop life, I'd always done a lot of writing, and he said - oh you can write, like that, and I looked at him, I said, of cou
rse I can write, I went to school.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 While you were at school did you have a part time job or any means of earning a little regular money?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, no. Nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You went straight from full time school?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. To full time - in the shop, yes. In the shop. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Your parents bought this shop and you started to work in it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What exactly did you have to do in the job?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We had knitting machines and I had to knit socks and re}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 
\af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 foot them, mend socks and stocking
s. I hated it. But I had to do it. Was part of it. And - it wasn't very long before mother was teaching me how to run a sewing machine, and learn to sew, for the benefit of the family and them later on for the benefit of the shop, you see, I could make ap
rons for home, I could make aprons to - to sell to people.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 But you looked after the shop as well, you were actually a shop assistant at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, chiefly. You see - it was next door to the house, you know, with a door in between so therefor
e - it wasn't a case of going the shop and stay in the shop. It was do this in the house and keep your ears open for the shop bell - to ring, it was in the house.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were in charge of the shop in fact were you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well - we - no, I wasn't in charge at first at thirteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Whenever the shop bell went it was up to you to go and see to it was it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That's right. Yes. Was my job. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What hours did you work, what were the opening hours of the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well roughly nine o'clock in th
e morning, unless somebody came knocking at the door - we - we officially opened at nine o'clock in the morning. But you didn't close until you were going to bed. Well somebody'd come knocking at the house door if you did, there'd be so - so - be somebody
 want something.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was a sort of drapery shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Drapery shop weren't it, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you open all day Saturday until bedtime?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Oh yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What about Sunday?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We didn't open Sunday. Definitely not. If they knocked at the door it
 happened once or twice, they knocked at the door for certain things, and my mother said now you write this note, she wasn't a very good writer, she knew what she wanted to put. You write this note. We were open until eleven o'clock last night, we are not
 open on Sundays, please not send any more. And that finished it.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you have any half days off during the week?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not - at the beginning. It hadn't come out hadn't the - and then - in those - there was a lawa passed, I forget what year it was pa
ssed, but it wasn't so at the beginning when - you had to have half a day. And that - that put my mother to do a bit of studying because - she couldn't make me go out in winter to be having me half day and it was a case of if the inspector came and found 
you - sewing or working what would happen, of course it - it wasn't as severe as that but - the newspapers and things had led you to believe that it would if the inspectors - coming around to see you at - when you got this half day.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You wouldn't have any holidays with pay because it was your own business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. Hadn't come at all, no.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What were you paid, were you paid a wage by your mother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Not until I was about - eighteen. And then - I was paid a wage - by my mother, equivalent to what m
e sister could earn in the mill. You see, we were going alternate, if I was working in the mill - well - she put me on board as she called it. Now you're eighteen you can keep yourself. But previous to that - well - your mother bought your clothes when sh
e thought you needed them, or - her said you can have this material if you'll make it - for yourself.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you didn't actually get a wage?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I didn't actually get a wage until I worked at the mill and - and until I was eighteen.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What was your mother like as an employer, did she keep you working much of the time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well fairly well because I think - there was so much work to do, with the house and her family as well, they - couldn't afford to sit down and do nothing.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How did you feel about the work, did you like it or dislike it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
I disliked the knitting. I liked sewing, and I didn't mind cooking and cleaning. Well in fact mother did most of the cooking, it was a case of - preparing you know, helping, doing the potatoes and things like that, and - and mind the shop in between.

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you like the shop work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh I liked the shop work, yes.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You did that job?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Of course that was after I was thirteen, you've gone on to afterwards haven't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You had the small shop at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Until 1912?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We went - at 1912. Yes. 1902. Not 1912. When I was twelve.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You moved from the little shop you had at Beechcliffe to a bigger shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh in the town.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In 1912 didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, that's right, that's 1912, yes. But previous to that I'd been a weaver. You see?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 While you were still at the small shop at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, but you see there was this other sister two years younger than me, so when she was able to leave school, she could st
op at home and help with the shop and I could go learn to weave, with an auntie who was willing to take me and teach me, how toweave. And then after some time, the other sister went to learn to weave and we alternated - for quite a few years. Between the 
one and the other, yes, that's right.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you were a weaver for so many months and a shop assistant for so many months?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. That is - that's how it was, yes, mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 As you say your mother made your wage up to what you'd be getting in weaving?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 She paid - that's right, to what - yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 In 1912 you moved from the little shop at Beechcliffe?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, we - we still kept the little shop, but we started the town shop. Yes. For me brother's benefit. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 When you took this bigger shop in town did you still work it on the same basis, you were still weaving part of the time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Oh no. I did - finished weaving then. I'd finished weaving when I was about - twenty or twenty-one, because there were so many inquiries for sewing - com
ing in it would help you see, because you see me brother was going out - around the countryside selling drapery because he hadn't been able to - get along with butchering. He couldn't get a job. And - and there were lots of things more to make, he used to
 bring orders back in you see. So really the - the sewing had become a fairly - full time }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 \endash }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180  back}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 
\ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 gr}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ound job, as you might say.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So the shop in Keighley kept you pretty well occupied?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. With the sewing we had you see.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 What happened to the shop at Beechcliffe then?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
My mother and the other sister. And the other sister - let me see - yes, she was courting at that time. You see, she married but he was in the forces, there was the war came, the 1914 war. And he was killed - in that war. So t
herefore - she was - always at home, she never - never got a home of her own because it was waiting until after the war, and of course he never came back. So it - it did continue - the little shop at Beechcliffe continued -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You lived there as well did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. We moved - we moved in 1923. Across - across the road onto Skipton Road, and gave the - that was to make mother give up shop}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 -}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 keeping. Because she was getting too old, it was to get her away from it. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Since the first world war what jobs have you done?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Only - only the shop in the town. After the war because you - you see it grew, the shop grew and the sewing grew, and - well it - yes, after the war we were - well began to employ other people as well. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you became a sort of manageress of it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was it owned jointly by you and your brother?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes. It was a joint undertaking, there were - there was - father with a share for father and mother. And - and me and him and the one sister - who had los
t her husband. Although she didn't work in it, but she put a little bit of money into it and - so she had a share. The youngest sisters at that time were a bit too young. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you took care of this shop in the centre until you married?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. And after. And after, I went on after I was married. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 How old were you when you finished working at the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Now then - I know I told somebody I'd been there thirty-four years, I was twenty-two, I'd be fifty-six.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were fifty-six when you eventually finished?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You retired then did you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So most of your married life you were busy with the shop?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Because, you see, work wasn't so good and he - he had a job which was insecure. And he di
dn't - it - well it was a - a - it would have been a bad thing to give up, insist on doing nothing, it was much better and we didn't have any family. Of course I was forty when I was married you see. Being quite honest we didn't try to have any family. Be
cause at forty - well it would have meant - start a family, I - with a man whose wage wasn't so good and was - rather insecure. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were better off keeping at work?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you worked until you were fifty-six and then you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You never did another job after?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, I never did anymore.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you sell the shop, was that why you retired?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 We didn't sell it then, I retired out and left it to the others. But you see me next - this 
seven - year - sister seven years younger than me had come into it, we'd also started another job - a shop at Bingley and she was - minding the shop at Bingley. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You were in quite a big way then by that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh - we were in quite a good w
ay of business, it's well known in Keighley, a lot of the older people say - I never forget your shop. Because it was everybody - a shop for everybody. A woman's shop chiefly. But - we sold - everything a woman could want. From vests, corsets, stockings -
 gloves - yes, not - not hats and coats. But blouses, jumpers, underwear, all kinds of underwear, yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you think looking back that you would have preferred another type of occupation? Had you had the choice.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, I don't think so. No. No, I lik
e people, you see, I like meeting people and - you certainly do meet a lot of people in a shop. Yes, especially if you're - you know - a - a person who is easy to know, we'll put it that way. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you didn't serve an apprenticeship or training period?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Well you learnt to be a weaver?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Yes, just - it just sort of grew up - I learnt the weaving. Which was a help in the - shop work afterwards. Well I could handle materials you see. If you'd been in a mill for a good few years you - y
ou understand the texture even by the touch - of materials.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you would never belong to a trade union?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Do you feel that there were divisions of interest among the workers at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There were what? Divisions?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Divisions of interest?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Not very much. No, not - not so much as - as perhaps is nowadays. They - they were more like - a group of younger sisters, we didn't have much trouble in the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you all worked together?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Some people s
ay that in those days there was a great division between trained craftsmen and other workers, do you feel that or not, at that time?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It isn't my experience. I wasn't - it might have applied in factories and places like that but it wasn't -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You didn't feel it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No, it wasn't in my experience.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say that full time work changed your general attitude to life any way?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, not - not the fact of it being full time work.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It was what went with it?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 It's what went wit
h it, you see, it made me work hard, because I had to work at home on - on the days off, on Tuesdays and things like that.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 I'd like to ask you now about your life at home after you left school. You continued to live at home didn't you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Would you say that starting full time work changed your relationship with your parents at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No, I don't think so really. I mean - the full time work in those days was so long - that - you - you hadn't a lot of time when you got home before it was
 time for bed. You see, the shops were open 'til nine o'clock at night, in those years, they were long days. And you didn't think anything about it. You went out to be there at nine o'clock in the morning and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So your relationship with your parents and your brother and sisters, you wouldn't say changed a great deal?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, not a great deal.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Only that you didn't have much time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 That's right. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you still spend Sunday at the chapel?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. I did until I married. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you take an interest in politics at all?
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, a little. A little, I went over to Labour. When Lee-Smith was putting up, my mother was upset. Because I said, well I said, he}{
\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid6619908\charrsid15471180 l}{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 ps far the better man. So I'm going to vote, it doesn't matter.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And he was called Lee Smith?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Was he the first Labour candidate in Keighley?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, he was and he went in with a - a great majority. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He was elected?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 As an MP?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes. Yes. But you see he was a capable man, he was an educated man. You know, and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 And he was a Labour candidate?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
He was a Labour candidate. But it was instead of having somebody who was half a gentleman or - quite a gentleman, who really - had - no knowledge of the - working people's - liv
es and outlook you know and I think that's why Lee Smith - really got a - he got in with a very good majority. I can't give you any figures now but - he didn't scrape in. No. And -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 This is why you supported him, because you felt he was for the working class?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 He was the - definitely the better man. Yes. The - to - whoever the other was who was being put up at the time, I can't just remember -

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So you would vote in 1918?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Somewhere about that time. Yes, I think it would be the first time I
 voted for a Parliament - in a Parliamentary election at all. Yes. Mm.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever feel under any pressure to vote for a particular party? Did your parents ever try to influence you at all?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No. No. No, I went to - I went to some meetings, you k
now, where there was speaking, and went home and said I'd been to these meetings and - it was oh what have they say or something, you see, they weren't - strongly - politically - out - strong political outlook. Not really.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 So they didn't try to influence you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
No. No, you - me mother just said, I didn't ever think you would have voted Labour. After which she didn't say any more, when I said, well - he is definitely a better man than the other man I think so I'm going to vote for him and - and -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You never joined a political party at that time?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Oh no. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You never worked for any party at an election?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you ever take any part in any political activity?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 No, you see there was another point of view there. It wasn't good -
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 The business?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes, it wasn't good policy. Yes. That's right. No.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You told me something earlier of how you spent your spare time, mainly reading and walking.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Yes.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 Did you continue to spend your spare time in the same way once you took the shop or did you do different things in your spare time?

\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 
Well, I didn't have much spare time but it went to the Sunday school what I did have. You see, I became a Sunday school teacher and - any - any spare time I had I was there.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You wouldn't be able to go out in the evenings would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 There was always the Tuesday you see, Tuesday that become a compulsory day then, but otherwise you were occupied with the shop.
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 On a Tuesday evening off you would be at the Sunday school would you?
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid5131904 OS  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 If there was anything going on there. Or otherwise I'd be at a friend's house or - in summer out for walks.
\par 
\par }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid13525481 I  : }{\rtlch\fcs1 \af0 \ltrch\fcs0 \insrsid10517864\charrsid15471180 You've already told me that you made lots of new friends once you started work?
